From 1a0003000000000000000000000000000000ob03 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Maintainers <goodhackersolutions@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] privacy: neutralize compiled-in telemetry/Normandy endpoints

SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

Belt-and-suspenders for the zero-telemetry invariant (CLAUDE.md security
invariant #1, docs/OpenBook-Browser-Build-Plan.md §10/§11). The locked
AutoConfig (config/autoconfig/openbook.cfg) already sets the telemetry/Normandy
enable flags off and blanks their server prefs. This patch additionally removes
the *compiled-in default endpoint URLs* from the all-prefs file so that even a
code path that ignored the runtime prefs has no Mozilla ingestion host baked in
to contact. Empty string = nowhere to phone home.

Endpoints neutralized: toolkit.telemetry.server (incoming.telemetry.mozilla.org),
app.normandy.api_url (normandy.cdn.mozilla.net), toolkit.coverage.endpoint.base,
and datareporting upload default flipped off.

NOTE: exact hunk context is rebased in CI against Firefox 145.0.2.
---
 modules/libpref/init/all.js | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/modules/libpref/init/all.js b/modules/libpref/init/all.js
index 5555555..6666666 100644
--- a/modules/libpref/init/all.js
+++ b/modules/libpref/init/all.js
@@ -2200,7 +2200,7 @@ pref("toolkit.telemetry.unified", true);
 // OpenBook: blank all compiled-in telemetry/experiment ingestion endpoints so
 // there is literally no Mozilla host to reach (docs §11). Runtime locks that
 // also disable the features live in openbook.cfg.
-pref("toolkit.telemetry.server", "https://incoming.telemetry.mozilla.org");
-pref("toolkit.coverage.endpoint.base", "https://coverage.mozilla.org");
-pref("app.normandy.api_url", "https://normandy.cdn.mozilla.net/api/v1");
-pref("datareporting.healthreport.uploadEnabled", true);
+pref("toolkit.telemetry.server", "");
+pref("toolkit.coverage.endpoint.base", "");
+pref("app.normandy.api_url", "");
+pref("datareporting.healthreport.uploadEnabled", false);
